Key Match Events: Amine Benaddi scored an own goal in the 35th minute, giving Australia a 1-0 lead.
Mitch Duke scored a header in the 61st minute, assisted by Craig Goodwin, to make it 2-0 for Australia.
Marco Tilio's left-footed shot from the right side of the box was saved in the top right corner in the 90'+4' minute.
Ali Hasan Isa's right-footed shot from outside the box missed to the right in the 90'+3' minute.
Mohammed Al Hardan (Bahrain) was shown a yellow card for a bad foul in the 90th minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Baniyas Stadium with an attendance of 300.
The final score was Bahrain 0, Australia 2.
